Challenge 2: Simple Menu System

Description:
Write a program that displays a simple menu to the user with options to: 
1) Print "Hello, World!", 
2) Print the current date and time, 
3) Exit. Use a for loop to repeatedly show the menu until the user chooses to exit. 
Use a switch statement to handle menu options.

Requirements:

Use a for loop to display the menu repeatedly.
Use a switch statement to handle menu choices.
Use the time package to print the current date and time.